arXiv.abstract:
  We derive the classical continuum limit of the operator tr$_s \sigma_{\mu\nu}
D^{ov}(x,x)$ with $D^{ov}$ being the overlap Dirac operator and show that it
corresponds to the gauge field strength tensor $F_{\mu\nu}(x)$.

A novel method to look for neutrino oscillations is proposed based on the elastic scattering process $ ar{
u}_{i} e^{-}ightarrow  ar{
u}_{i} e^{-}$, taking advantage of the dynamical zero present in the differential cross section for $ ar{
u}_{e} e^{-}ightarrow  ar{
u}_{e} e^{-}$. An effective tunable experiment between the "appearance" and "disappearance" limits is made possible. Prospects to exclude the allowed region for atmospheric neutrino oscillations are given.
